title: Simone Biles wins her 6th world all-around gold medal, breaking her own record
description: Ten years after she won her first world title in Antwerp, Belgium, at age 16, Simone Biles added another all-around gold medal to her collection Friday in the same city where it all began.

title: NBA can shift the balance of power in media with its next rights deal
description: The National Basketball Association’s upcoming decision on which companies will acquire the TV and streaming rights for its live games could transform the entire media industry.

title: Iranian human rights activist Narges Mohammadi wins Nobel Peace Prize for fight against 'oppression of women'
description: Iranian human rights activist Narges Mohammadi won the Nobel Peace Prize on Friday for her fight against women's oppression in Iran and advocating for human rights.

title: During an online fundraiser, Matt Gaetz denounced the Biden impeachment effort as unserious
description: Rep. Matt Gaetz and Rep. Matt Rosendale denounced as a political stunt Republicans’ high-stakes effort to impeach President Joe Biden.

title: It's not just long Covid: Symptoms can linger after other illnesses, leading to 'long colds'
description: How long do cold and flu symptoms last? New research finds that lingering cold symptoms can lead to a syndrome similar to long Covid, in this case, long colds.

title: Russia is taking a beating in the Black Sea. Is it plotting a new escalation?
description: Russia is seeking to target cargo ships carrying grain in the Black Sea, the U.K. says, planning to cover up the attacks by blaming them on Ukraine.

title: One-on-one with Taylor Lorenz
description: It started out as a way to grow person brands from home. Now, it’s turned into a multi-billion dollar global industry. But are influencers starting to lose their influence now that they’re getting paid? Stephanie Ruhle sits down one-on-one with Taylor Lorenz to find out and discuss her new book, “Extremely Online.”

title: New Jersey AG's public integrity unit reviewing handling of fatal crash involving Sen. Menendez's wife
description: New Jersey state investigators are now reviewing how officials handled a deadly 2018 car crash involving the woman who is now Sen. Bob Menendez's wife.

title: Cyberattack cost MGM Resorts about $100 million, Las Vegas company says
description: The criminal cyberattack on MGM Resorts in Las Vegas last month resulted in the company losing around $100 million, it said in a Thursday evening filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission.

title: Biden administration to resume direct deportation flights for Venezuelan migrants
description: The U.S. government has already identified people in federal custody who “will be removed promptly in the coming days,” a senior Biden administration official said.
